This is already implemented. The middleware at `src/middleware.ts` handles this:

```typescript
const isPublicRoute = createRouteMatcher(["/", "/sign-in(.*)", "/sign-up(.*)"]);

export default clerkMiddleware(async (auth, request) => {
  if (!isPublicRoute(request)) {
    await auth.protect();
  }
});
```

`auth.protect()` is called for any route not in the public list, which means `/dashboard` and `/settings` are already protected. Unauthenticated users hitting those routes are automatically redirected to `/sign-in` (configured via `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in` in your `.env`).

You can verify by visiting `/dashboard` in an incognito window — you'll be redirected to the sign-in page.
